.Dd May 18, 2026
.Dt ZM 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm zm
.Nd Z-Manager archive utility
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar options
.Ar command
.Nm
.Fl cf
.Ar archive
.Op Ar create-options
.Ar paths ...
.Nm
.Fl xf
.Ar archive
.Op Ar extract-options
.Nm
.Fl tf
.Ar archive
.Op Ar list-options
.Nm
.Fl Tf
.Ar archive
.Op Ar test-options
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
creates, extracts, lists, tests, and plans archives.
The public command surface is designed for scriptable stdout and human-readable
diagnostics on stderr.
.Pp
ZIP, TAR.ZST, TZAP, and 7z have native backends.
RAR extraction uses the bundled extraction-only RAR backend.
Other supported archive formats fall back to libarchive.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width "formats"
.It Cm create Ar archive Ar paths ...
Create an archive.
.It Cm extract Ar archive
Extract an archive.
.It Cm list Ar archive
List archive contents.
.It Cm test Ar archive
Test archive readability or integrity.
.It Cm plan Ar paths ...
Show what
.Cm create
would archive.
.It Cm formats
Show supported archive formats.
.It Cm doctor
Verify the installed CLI and archive engine.
.It Cm completions Ar bash|zsh|fish|powershell
Print a shell completion script.
.It Cm help Op Ar command
Show top-level help or command-specific help.
.El
.Sh GLOBAL OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--no-password-prompt"
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Show help.
.It Fl V , Fl -version
Show version.
.It Fl q , Fl -quiet
Reduce output.
.It Fl v , Fl -verbose
Increase diagnostics.
.It Fl -json
Emit JSON where supported.
.It Fl -color Cm auto Ns | Ns Cm always Ns | Ns Cm never
Control color output for human-readable help, summaries, diagnostics, and
progress.
The default
.Cm auto
colors terminal streams and honors
.Ev NO_COLOR .
.Cm always
forces color and
.Cm never
disables it.
.It Fl -no-color
Alias for
.Fl -color Cm never .
.It Fl -progress Cm auto Ns | Ns Cm always Ns | Ns Cm never
Control progress output.
.It Fl -no-progress
Alias for
.Fl -progress Cm never .
.It Fl -no-password-prompt
Fail instead of prompting interactively.
.It Fl c , Fl -create
Create an archive in classic syntax.
.It Fl x , Fl -extract
Extract an archive in classic syntax.
.It Fl t , Fl -list
List archive contents in classic syntax.
.It Fl T , Fl -test
Test archive integrity in classic syntax.
.It Fl f , Fl -file Ar archive
Archive file path in classic syntax.
.El
.Sh CREATE OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--preserve-symlinks"
.It Fl r , Fl -recursive
Accepted for ZIP familiarity; directories recurse by default.
.It Fl C , Fl -directory Ar dir
Use
.Ar dir
as the base for following input paths.
.It Fl @
Read input paths from stdin.
.It Fl -files-from Ar file|-
Read input paths from a file, or stdin with
.Sq - .
.It Fl -null
Read NUL-delimited path lists with
.Fl @
or
.Fl -files-from .
.It Fl -clean
Apply clean source exclusions.
.It Fl -no-ignore
Ignore
.Pa .gitignore
and default exclusion rules.
.It Fl -hidden
Accepted for compatibility; hidden files are included by default.
.It Fl -no-hidden
Exclude hidden dotfiles.
.It Fl i , Fl -include Ar glob
Include archive paths matching
.Ar glob .
.It Fl -exclude Ar glob
Exclude archive paths matching
.Ar glob .
.It Fl -exclude-from Ar file
Read exclude globs from
.Ar file .
.It Fl -format Cm zip Ns | Ns Cm tar.zst Ns | Ns Cm tzap Ns | Ns Cm 7z
Override format inference from the archive extension.
.It Fl -method Ar method
Select compression method.
.It Fl -level Ar level
Compression level.
.It Fl 0 ... Fl 9
Compression presets; level 0 stores ZIP entries.
.It Fl -store
Store ZIP entries without compression.
.It Fl -solid
Use solid 7z mode.
.It Fl -no-solid
Disable solid 7z mode.
.It Fl -volume-size Ar size
Split ZIP or 7z output into volumes.
Sizes accept bytes or
.Cm k ,
.Cm m ,
.Cm g ,
and
.Cm t
suffixes.
ZIP writes
.Pa .z01/.zip
sets; 7z writes
.Pa .7z.001
sets.
.It Fl j , Fl -junk-paths
Store basenames only; fail if flattened names collide.
.It Fl y , Fl -preserve-symlinks
Store symlink entries where the backend supports them.
.It Fl -follow-symlinks
Archive symlink target contents.
.It Fl -preserve-metadata
Preserve portable metadata where supported.
.It Fl X , Fl -no-metadata
Omit portable metadata where supported.
.It Fl -force
Replace an existing output archive.
.It Fl -dry-run
Print planned entries without writing the archive.
.It Fl T , Fl -test-after
Test the archive after writing.
.It Fl -encrypt
Prompt for an archive password where supported.
.It Fl -password-stdin
Read one password line from stdin.
TZAP archives are encrypted; use
.Fl -encrypt
or
.Fl -password-stdin
when creating them.
.El
