.Sh GLOB FILTERS
Glob patterns match archive paths after command-specific path processing.
Quote patterns so the shell does not expand them first.
Use
.Sq dir/**
for a whole tree;
.Sq *
can match
.Sq / .
.Sh SUPPORTED FORMATS
.Bl -tag -width "tar.zst"
.It Cm zip
Create
.Pa .zip ;
extract/list/test
.Pa .zip ,
.Pa .zipx ,
.Pa .jar ,
.Pa .war ,
.Pa .ipa ,
.Pa .apk ,
.Pa .appx ,
and
.Pa .xpi .
.It Cm tar.zst
Create and extract
.Pa .tar.zst
and
.Pa .tzst .
.It Cm tzap
Create, extract, list, and test passphrase-protected
.Pa .tzap
archives.
.It Cm 7z
Create and extract
.Pa .7z .
.It Cm raw
Extract raw single-file streams:
.Pa .zst ,
.Pa .gz ,
.Pa .bz2 ,
.Pa .xz ,
.Pa .lzma ,
.Pa .lz ,
.Pa .br ,
.Pa .lz4 ,
.Pa .lzo ,
.Pa .Z ,
and
.Pa .lrz .
.It Cm rar
Extract
.Pa .rar
and
.Pa .cbr .
Passworded RAR list/extract uses the bundled RAR backend with
.Fl -password-stdin .
.It Cm fallback
Other libarchive-supported formats.
.El
.Sh PASSWORD HANDLING
Passwords should flow through stdin or the interactive prompt.
Do not pass passwords as command arguments.
Use
.Fl -password-stdin
with a single line on stdin in scripts.
.Sh SHELL COMPLETIONS
Release packages install bash, zsh, and fish completions where supported.
For manual setup, print the completion script for a shell:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
source <(zm completions bash)
zm completions zsh > ~/.zfunc/_zm
zm completions fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/zm.fish
zm completions powershell > zm.ps1
.Ed
.Sh STDOUT AND JSON
Human diagnostics, progress, and errors are written to stderr.
Data modes such as
.Fl -to-stdout
and JSON modes write their payloads to stdout.
JSON and raw data payloads are never colorized.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width "2"
.It 0
Success.
.It 1
Operation failed.
.It 2
Usage error.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
zm -cf project.zip project/
zm create source.tar.zst src README.md --format tar.zst
zm extract project.zip -C out/ --include 'docs/**'
zm extract project.tar.zst --strip-components 1 -C out/
zm list project.zip --tree
zm test project.zip --json
printf '%s\n' "$ZM_PASSWORD" | zm create secret.7z private/ --encrypt --password-stdin
printf '%s\n' "$RAR_PASSWORD" | zm extract secret.rar -C out/ --password-stdin
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr tar 1 ,
.Xr zip 1
